s highflyer that split its stock again and again during the dot-com boom. W=
hen the telecom bubble burst, JDS Uniphase reported a loss of roughly $50 b=
illion for fiscal 2001, including a nearly $39 billion write-down for overp=
riced acquisitions, a record loss for a US company at the time.

JDS Uniphase split into Lumentum and Viavi Solutions in 2015.

