<td align=3D"left" style=3D"padding:5px;Margin:0">
<p style=3D"Margin:0;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;-ms-text-size-adjust:non=
e;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;font-family:roboto, 'helvetica neue', helvet=
ica, arial, sans-serif;line-height:24px;color:#333333;font-size:16px">Lumen=
tum makes the lasers and optical parts that move data around as pulses of l=
ight, the technology that shuttles information between the chips inside AI =
data centers and across the buildings that house them. It was spun out of t=
elecom-equipment maker JDS Uniphase back in 2015, and for years it was a fa=
irly sleepy supplier tied to phone networks and the sensors behind Apple's =
Face ID. The AI boom changed everything. Analysts now expect revenue to cli=
mb from about $1.6 billion in fiscal 2025 to over $8 billion by fiscal 2028=
, roughly a 5x jump, with growth topping 80% in each of the next two years.=
</p></td>
