ost recent quarter saw revenue jump about 90% to a record $808 million, led=
 by these parts as customers upgrade their networks to faster standards. Tw=
o newer products add fuel: optical circuit switches, which let data centers=
 rewire their connections on the fly to save power, and co-packaged optics,=
 which build the light-handling pieces directly onto chips. Switch backlog =
alone has already passed $400 million.</p>
<p style=3D"Margin:0;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;-ms-text-size-adjust:non=
